Durban - A KwaZulu-Natal man accused of being involved in the disappearance of a police officer was convicted and sentenced to 39 years imprisonment. Siyabonga Khumalo, 39, was sentenced to 25 years for murder, 10 years for armed robbery and four years for kidnapping. His accomplices, Lucky Masinga, 32, and Thandazile Zikhali, 37, are still in custody and will appear on May 18. In February, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, police spokesperson, said Constable Senzeni Msiphaâ€™s vehicle was found burnt in the Nyoni area with a body inside, believed to be the missing police officer. Police said they are still waiting for the DNA results to confirm identity. It is alleged that Msipha never returned home after going shopping at the Gingindlovu Mall on January 31. At the time of her disappearance, she was driving her Ford Fiesta. She was last seen wearing a blue t-shirt and black sandals. Msipha was stationed at Mthunzini police station. Daily News